From 1c4995b9807cceb4b4afa983fa8c3cc222d84255 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ferdinando Terada <Ferdinando.GodoyTerada@windriver.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 09:33:35 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] add OVS access bridge setup scripts

Add two Python scripts to manage a Linux bridge (ovs0) and
associated veth pairs for interfaces flagged with ovs-access
in their stx-description field.

create_ovs_access (if-pre-up.d):
- Parses /etc/network/interfaces.d/ifcfg-$IFACE looking for
  a stx-description line containing ovs-access=<ethdev>
- Creates the ovs0 Linux bridge if it does not exist
- Creates a veth pair (<ifname> / <ifname>-ovs) and attaches
  the -ovs end to the bridge
- Attaches the specified ethernet device to the bridge
- Verifies all interfaces and the bridge are UP
- Creates/updates /etc/ovs-access-monitor/ovs-access-monitor.conf
  with the correct failover_interface value
- Starts or restarts ovs-access-monitor.service

delete_ovs_access (if-post-down.d):
- Reverses the operations of create_ovs_access
- Stops ovs-access-monitor.service if active
- Detaches the ethernet device from the bridge
- Deletes the veth pair
- The ovs0 bridge is intentionally left in place

Both scripts follow the existing ifupdown-extra logging convention:
messages go to syslog (daemon facility) when DO_SYSLOG=yes, or
to stdout/stderr otherwise, matching the do_output() pattern
used by the other scripts in this package.

Packaging:
- debian/dirs: add if-pre-up.d and if-post-down.d entries
- debian/ifupdown-extra.install: register both new scripts
- debian/rules: install both scripts with mode 0755

Signed-off-by: Andre Kantek <andrefernandozanella.kantek@windriver.com>
